external_knowledge:
- 'actively engaged' refers to users with a status of 'active';
- 'shared their findings' implies that the user has reports with a status of 'published';
- 'set their dashboards to public view' means that the user's dashboards have a status of 'published'.

sql:
SELECT users.username 
FROM users 
WHERE users.id IN (
    SELECT dashboards.user_id 
    FROM dashboards 
) 
AND users.id NOT IN (
    SELECT reports.user_id 
    FROM reports
);

external_knowledge:
- 'whispers from the bustling market floor' refers to the latest market data;
- 'financial phoenixes' refers to the cryptocurrencies;
- 'dance of the most recent data' means the most up-to-date live data where `is_live = 1`.

sql:
SELECT name, market_cap
FROM cryptocurrencies
ORDER BY market_cap DESC;

SELECT symbol, volume_change_24h
FROM market_data
ORDER BY symbol;

SELECT visualization_name 
FROM visualizations 
WHERE LENGTH(visualization_name) = (
    SELECT MAX(LENGTH(visualization_name)) 
    FROM visualizations
);
